We propose a scan-statistic approach, WGScan, for the analysis of whole-genome sequencing data. WGScan can simultaneously detect the existence, and estimate the locations of the association signals at genome-wide scale (or in a pre-specified large region). Specifically, given a study population of n subjects, with Yi being the quantitative/dichotomous outcome value; Xi = (Xi1, …, Xid)T being the d covariates, which can include age, gender, principal components of genetic variation etc.; {Gij}1≤j≤p being the p genetic variants in the region of interest, we are interested in simultaneous determining the windows Φkl = {j:k ≤ j ≤ l} where the signals reside and testing the association between Yi and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
